      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your reflection staring back at you can be a harsh reminder of how lost you feel. It's as if your old spark and plans were buried under the weight of time, and now you're just carrying on autopilot. It's exhausting to pretend to be someone you're no longer. Allowing yourself to acknowledge this loss and process the grief might be the first step towards rediscovering the spark within.",
